  "body": "## What's The Problem\r\nOne of the most frustrating issues with BigNumber is that I can't prettify a BigNumber into a readable format. For example, if I was using Hardhat console to print out a BigNumber, I would get `999999999999999999292` as string format. This is difficult to read.\r\n\r\n## Proposed Solution\r\nIf Hardhat extended BN.js with an additional function to format a BigNumber into a readable format, it would make it easier for developers to read these BigNumbers.\r\n\r\nFor example, the following code shows (I'm sure there are many ways to do this) how to convert this BigNumber to a readable format:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nbigNumber.toString().replace(/\\B(?=(\\d{3})+(?!\\d))/g, \",\")\r\n\r\n// bigNumber as a string:                  999999999999999999292 \r\n// bigNumber using the format above:       999,999,999,999,999,999,292\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
